definition.value: A racemate comprising equal amounts of (R)- and (S)-triadimefon. A fungicide used to control powdery mildew, rusts and other infections in crops.

A member of the class of triazoles that is 3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butane-1,2-diol substituted at position O1 by a 4-chlorophenyl group. A fungicide for cereals, beet and brassicas used to control a range of diseases including powdery mildew, rusts, bunts and smuts.
